<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4cfdb531-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12221"><num value="12221">§ 12221.</num><heading> Grant authorization</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id4cfdb532-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12221/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Attorney General may make grants to State, Indian tribal, or local prosecutors for the purpose of supporting the creation or expansion of community-based justice programs.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id4cfdb533-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s12221/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Consultation</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Attorney General may consult with the Ounce of Prevention Council in making grants under subsection (a).</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id4cfdb534-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/322/tIII/s31701">Pub. L. 103–322, title III, § 31701</ref>, <date date="1994-09-13">Sept. 13, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/1890">108 Stat. 1890</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id4cfdb535-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">
